-- Iraq Awards Turkey’s UB Holding Steel Plant Rehabilitation
-- B y   K h a l i d   A l - A n s a r y
-- 2012-08-28T08:21:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/iraq-awards-turkey-s-ub-holding-steel-plant-rehabilitation.html
Iraq’s cabinet agreed to award
 Turkey ’s  UB Holding  a project to rehabilitate a steel plant in
the south of the Persian Gulf country, according to an official
at the Iraqi Ministry of Industry and Minerals.  The government will sign the contract with UB Holding
within a month, Amer Abdel Razzaq, deputy director general of
the ministry’s investment department, said in a telephone
interview in  Baghdad  today.  UB Holding will spend about $500 million for the first
phase of the rehabilitation plan of the steel plant in the
province of Basra, Abdel Razzaq said in a June 19 interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Khalid Al-Ansary in Dubai at 
 kalansary@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
